  "prompt": "Is there a way to see someones likes on instagram?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, Instagram does not provide a built-in feature that allows users to view a comprehensive list of another person's liked posts. Here's what you should know:\n\n### **What You Can See:**\n\n1. **Likes on Specific Posts:**\n   - When you visit a particular post on Instagram, you can see who has liked that specific post. If the user has liked it, their username will appear in the list of likes for that post.\n\n2. **Activity on Stories and Highlights:**\n   - While Instagram Stories show who has viewed them, they do not display likes in the same way as regular posts.\n\n### **What You **Cannot** See:**\n\n- **Comprehensive Likes List:**\n  - There is no feature on Instagram that allows you to view an entire history of all the posts a specific user has liked. This information is kept private to protect user privacy.\n\n### **Third-Party Tools and Risks:**\n\n- **Caution Against Third-Party Apps:**\n  - Some third-party applications or websites may claim to offer the ability to view someone else's liked posts. However, using such tools poses significant risks:\n    - **Privacy Concerns:** These tools often require access to your Instagram account, which can compromise your personal information.\n    - **Violation of Instagram\u2019s Terms of Service:** Utilizing unauthorized apps can lead to penalties, including account suspension or banning.\n    - **Security Risks:** There's a high chance these services are scams designed to steal your data or spread malware.\n\n### **Protecting Your Privacy:**\n\n- **Secure Your Account:**\n  - Always use strong, unique passwords and enable two-factor authentication to safeguard your Instagram account.\n  \n- **Review App Permissions:**\n  - Regularly check which third-party apps have access to your Instagram account and revoke access to any that you do not recognize or no longer use.\n\n### **Stay Updated:**\n\n- **Instagram\u2019s Features Evolve:**\n  - Social media platforms frequently update their features and privacy settings. To stay informed about any changes to Instagram's privacy policies or new features related to likes and activity visibility, regularly check Instagram\u2019s [official blog](https://about.instagram.com/blog/) or [Help Center](https://help.instagram.com/).\n\n### **Conclusion:**\n\nCurrently, Instagram prioritizes the privacy of user interactions, including likes. While you can see if someone has liked a specific post, there is no official method to view a complete list of all the posts a user has liked. Be cautious of third-party services that claim to offer this functionality, as they may compromise your privacy and security.\n\nIf you have further questions or need assistance with Instagram features, feel free to ask!",
